data.title: Dr. Antoanella Calame named in San Diego's 2025 "Top Doctors" list for Dermatopathology.
data.description: In San Diego on October 30, 2025, Compass Dermatopathology is pleased to reveal that its leader, Antoanella Calame, MD, a certified dermatologist and dermatopathologist, has been recognized as one of the "Top Doctors" in Dermatopathology for the year 2025.

data.title: Timberland Bancorp's 2025 fiscal year net income increased to $29.16 million EPS rose to $3.67. A new branch in University Place announced.
data.description: Timberland Bancorp, Inc. reported strong financial results with net income increasing 20% to $29.16 million for the fiscal year ended September 30, 2025. Earnings per diluted common share ("EPS") increased by 22% to $3.67. Quarterly EPS increased by 19% to $1.07. Quarterly net interest margin increased to 3.82%, Return on Average Assets to 1.68%, and Return on Average Equity to 12.97%. The company announced an 8% increase in the quarterly cash dividend to $0.28 per share and plans to open a branch in University Place. Total assets reached $2.0 billion with a 3% increase, while total deposits increased by 3% and shareholders' equity increased by 2%. Non-performing assets to total assets ratio was 0.23%. Timberland originated $100.09 million in loans during the quarter. Total deposits increased by $47.16 million to $1.72 billion. Total shareholders' equity increased by 2% to $262.61 million. The company remains well capitalized with a total risk-based capital ratio of 20.67% and a Tier 1 leverage capital ratio of 12.59%.

data.title: Buenaventura announces Q3 & 9M 2025 results, Peru's largest metals mining company. Figures in USD, prepared under IFRS.
data.description: Peru's largest publicly-traded precious metals mining company, Compañia de Minas Buenaventura S.A.A., released its financial results for the third quarter and nine-month period ending on September 30, 2025. The figures, reported in U.S. dollars (US$) and prepared according to International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) on a non-GAAP basis, show the company's performance during 3Q25 and 9M25. Buenaventura is listed on the New York Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol BVN and on the Lima Stock Exchange under BUE.LM.

data.title: ThreeD Capital Inc renews investor relations agreement with PHK Investments LLC, paying £6,875/month and £20,000/month in ad spend. Also issues 100,000 stock options at $0.40/share.
data.description: ThreeD Capital Inc. has extended its agreement with PHK Investments LLC to provide investor relations services, replacing the previous arrangement that expired on October 8, 2025. Under the new Agreement, ThreeD will pay a fixed monthly fee of £6,875 (approximately $12,640 CAD) and up to £20,000 (approximately $36,772 CAD) in monthly ad spend. The Company will also issue 100,000 stock options exercisable at $0.40 per share. Half of the options vest in six months and the rest in 12 months, expiring two years from the grant date if unexercised.

data.title: Consensys taps JPMorgan and Goldman Sachs to lead upcoming IPO, as regulatory environment for crypto firms in the US improves.
data.description: Consensys, a blockchain company, is intending to go public through an Initial Public Offering (IPO), with major financial institutions JPMorgan and Goldman Sachs heading the underwriting. This decision comes as regulatory certainty for crypto-related companies in the United States is on the rise.

data.title: Bright Minds Biosciences, Inc. will present at conferences to discuss 5-HT2 agonists for CNS disorders.
data.description: Today, on October 30, 2025, Bright Minds Biosciences, Inc. (NASDAQ: DRUG), a leading company specializing in the development of precise 5-HT2 agonists for drug-resistant epilepsy, depression, and various central nervous system disorders, revealed its plans to participate in upcoming conferences. This includes a focus on creating effective treatments for conditions such as drug-resistant epilepsy and depression.

data.title: Coach Trenton Hassell of Clarksville Christian School wins National Coach of the Year for girls' basketball with four state wins.
data.description: In a surprising turn of events on October 30, 2025, in Clarksville, Tennessee, Trenton Hassell, the head coach of the girls' basketball team at Clarksville Christian School and a former NBA player, received the esteemed National Coach of the Year award from the National Christian School Association. This recognition marks a significant achievement for Hassell, showcasing his exceptional coaching abilities.

data.title: Lumen Technologies (NYSE: LUMN) stock rises post Q3 earnings report, surpassing analyst estimates. 20 cent EPS loss, $3.08B revenue.
data.description: Shares of Lumen Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: LUMN) surged following the release of its third-quarter earnings report after the market closed on Thursday. The company exceeded expectations on both the top and bottom lines. LUMN stock saw an uptick in response. The report revealed quarterly losses of 20 cents per share, outperforming the anticipated losses of 27 cents per share by analysts. Additionally, quarterly revenue stood at $3.08 billion, surpassing the analyst consensus estimate of $3.03 billion. For more in-depth coverage, the full story can be accessed on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Cloudflare (NYSE: NET) stock rises on Q3 earnings report. Beat Street estimate with 27 cents per share and revenue of $562.02M.
data.description: Cloudflare Inc. (NYSE: NET) saw a rise in shares following the release of its Q3 earnings report. The stock experienced an increase, with quarterly earnings at 27 cents per share, surpassing the Street's forecast of 23 cents. Cloudflare's Q3 revenue totaled $562.02 million. For real-time price updates on NET stock, refer to the stock exchange. Check out more details regarding this news update. Discover further insights on the full story at Benzinga.com.

data.title: Partnership formed by IIP and Nissan Chemical America to distribute nanoActiv® technology for Enhanced Oil Recovery in MENA.
data.description: In Abu Dhabi, UAE, on October 30, 2025, International Industrial Partners (IIP) revealed a new collaboration with Nissan Chemical America to distribute nanoActiv® technology. This groundbreaking technology is known for being the first brine-resistant innovation globally. This partnership aims to market and distribute nanoActiv® to a wider audience through IIP's network.

data.title: Mastercard plans to acquire Zerohash for stablecoin growth with $2 billion deal, enhancing settlement options.
data.description: It has been reported that Mastercard is close to finalizing a purchase agreement worth $2 billion to buy Zerohash, a company specializing in crypto infrastructure. The goal of this acquisition is to strengthen Mastercard's stablecoin and on-chain settlement functionalities.

data.title: Ziegler prices $34M Series 2025 Bonds for Carol Woods retirement center in Chapel Hill, NC.
data.description: Ziegler has happily disclosed the effective pricing of a total of $34,000,000 Series 2025 Bonds for The Chapel Hill Residential Retirement Center, Inc., operating as Carol Woods. Established in July 1972, Carol Woods is a nonprofit organization in North Carolina.

data.title: Nektar Therapeutics will be at the Jefferies Global Healthcare Conference in London on Nov 17-20, 2025. #NKTR
data.description: Nektar Therapeutics (Nasdaq: NKTR) has disclosed that its management will be webcasting their involvement at the Jefferies Global Healthcare Conference taking place from November 17-20, 2025 in London. This announcement was made in San Francisco on October 30, 2025. This move aims to showcase the company's presence at the significant event, providing insights into their contributions to the conference.
